posts.name: Ravi Ponmalai
posts.cooked: I love the diffy wrist so much, it was so cool to see at Chezy. I see you all wrote your own control scheme for the differential mechanism instead of using the Phoenix 6 control request. Would you recommend doing that in the future?

posts.name: Tim Swartz
posts.cooked:
No we just didn‚Äôt know those existed we wanted to play with it over summer but ran out of time doing other things with elevator optimization. We lost our senior programmer so our two programmers with 1 year experience had to figure out our code base more and learn some new things on top of that as well. We may look into this but don‚Äôt plan to use diffys as our go to mechanism for every problem and have other things we want to work on that aren‚Äôt as niche.

I wouldn‚Äôt say we do it better than what the simple or advanced diffy control can do. CTRE software team is pro and I bet it would be faster/more control but this worked for us and it didn‚Äôt hamper our robot performance but maybe if we wanted to simplify it and improve it would help. TLDR use ctre diffy if you can

posts.name: Alumni of team 2930
posts.cooked:
An awesome and competitive robot from an amazing team. I loved watching your robot and working with your team at Glacier Peak, Sundome and DCMP . I can‚Äôt wait to look through all of this!

For my question: At Chezy Champs, your playoffs alliance used the processor algae strategy (which was very fun to watch). How did the team come up with that and how did they  decide when to use it?

posts.name: Tim Swartz
posts.cooked: The first time we used it we knew we were down on raw points and if we played 3-O v 3-O we would lose. Bread (5940) suggested it because they did it earlier that year in one match and it was effective at throwing them off. Looking at match 67 at Chezy we missed two processor shots due to it being fuller. We saw how the strategy could work and each algae missed was worth 6 for us and it also made any algae they missed robot wise flip into another 6 for us. I think this strategy only works at high level and even then you just need to not score in net and both teams put in processor to avoid having all 18 in one net.
